We generally see competition as a healthy and necessary mechanism for progress, particularly in sports and business, provided it is conducted fairly and doesn't come at the expense of mateship or collective well-being. Because of this, our view is pragmatic: we lean toward competition being a positive, constructive force, but it must be tempered by humility and fairness.

